      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WYONG DALLAS (3) is back from a seven months break after failing to finish last time but prior to that was a Special conditions race winner in quick time (29.32) at Sandown. Rates strongly on best and well worth another try. SLICK TOMMY (1) missed the frame and safely held latest finishing 8th at Bendigo following on from a win (25.83) at Geelong the start prior. The form out of last race has been strong. Should be about the money. ZIPPING ARVADA (7) was long overdue after four placings in a row before a deserved win (19.95) last time at Traralgon. Form here at the trip excellent including three wins. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. ASTON FONTAINE (6) impressed last start, winning in good time. Must include.",
